Tanzanian songbird Saida Karoli is expected to feature in two musical shows in Nairobi and Kisumu next month. This will be her comeback show to the Kenyan music scene, having kept a low profile for a while and will be promoting her new album. Karoli will arrive in Kenya on December 4. The show, titled "African Music Extravaganza," will feature musicians from Kenya, Tanzania and DR Congo. This is her second time in Kenya since 2004. Her first show will be held at the Meladen Club in Nairobiâ€™s Upper Hill on December 7. Also expected for the show is upcoming Congolese star Rice Matadien, who was formerly with Ferre Gola. The Nairobi-based Rhumba Japan band, also from Congo, and Kenyan ohangla star Musa Jakadala will also entertain rumba fans. Karoli will then tour Kisumu on December 14.